title: UCI ProGrRT National -- Plattekill Mtn. Gravity Op
Kreb Cycle Friday Night Race Series
description: The Kreb Cycle Friday Night race series uses Ring Road on the campus of Suffolk Community College in Riverhead. We have circuit races, time trials, points races, and a Team Time Trial. We have A (Category 2-4), B (Category 4-5), or C (Category 5 and one day) races. A race is usually 20 laps, B 15 laps and C 10 laps. Sometimes the races are shortened due to darkness. We usually try to have a longer race around Summer Solstice. The Friday Night Races have been held for 29 consecutive years.
course: Each lap is about 1.9 miles. 2 gentle, maybe 40ft of climbing per lap.
registration: Registration begins @ 5:30 and closes @ 6pm. We have a field limit of 45 in the A race 35 in the B race and 20 in the C race. Fee is $15. $5 unattached fee.
notes:
We race in the rain but not lightning. If there are less than 10 people per field we will combine or cancel the race. Ex. if it\'s pouring and 2 riders show up I\'m not going to stand out there holding up lap cards for those knuckleheads. 
Prize money is a percentage of the registration. The more riders in your race the more prize money there is. Top 5 places in the A race top 3 in the B race. We do have primes for both groups. Please don\'t come here looking to take home next months mortgage payment. We have no electronic timing, no camera. The idea is to provide you a place to race without a big entry fee. It\'s like a little laboratory where you can practice some tactics that you might not want to experiment with at a weekend race. Try your sprint a little earlier...... a little later, take a flyer with 1.5 to go, use 3 riders for a leadout. Ride a team time trial!! 
Not saying that we don\'t try to put on a good event for you, the resources are limited though. If your looking for big prize money and all that electronic timing stuff, or if you need a result sheet to tell if you were 14th or 15th maybe you should find a different place to race.
directions: CR 51 in Riverhead to Riverhead Speonk Road. Follow signs to college. Upon entering college make left at first stop sign. Then first right into parking field. Registration is in that first parking field.

title: Whiteface 5 K Downhill
description: This years 5 K DH is a New York State Championship Event, and is also the NY State finals between Plattekill & Whiteface Mountains.
course:
Downhill course will be classic Whiteface downhill with a speed section to start followed by technical dh single-track. This race course mixes things up and is like 4 race course in 1(Approx. 3.1 miles) There will be 1 course for all categories.
Note. Open practice will be available on downhill course until 1 hour prior to the start of the race.
registration:
Registration will be available online @ www.active.com for a $15.00 savings off of the on-site registration cost.
Online price is $65.00 for amateurs and $80.00 for pros. All registration includes your required 2 day lift pass. Online registration will be available from July 1st until September 8th.
notes: After the main dh event we will once again host a chainless dh race. The chainless dh is a \"For Fun\" race only and no USAC points will be awarded. The cost to race in the chainless dh will be an additional $10.00. Only those registered in the main event are eligible to register for the chainless.
directions: Route 86 in Wilmington, N.Y. 12997. Only 8 miles from Lake Placid. Plenty of camping,lodging and dining right in Wilmington!

title: Nancy Morgenstern Memorial 2011 Fall Bear Mountain
Clarkson MTB Series
description: A mtb training series for collegiate riders and the community.
course: 90% singletrack with few rocky sections and many tight turns. 10% smooth wide double track. The course will start off with approximately 100 yards of double track before heading into singletrack for about 3.5 miles. then a short section of doubletrack into another 1.5 miles of singletrack and then finishing with a 1/4 mile of doubletrack to the beginning of the loop. Soil is variable from loam to sand to silt and many sections will be muddy if there has been recent rain.
directions: Race start is at the Clarkson University trails.

title: Cyclocross and Fall Festival at the Apple Farm
description: Welcome to the first edition of the Fall Festival and Cyclocross Race.  We\'ve brought together some of the areas finest art&crafts, as well as food vendors to create a festive race atmosphere.
course: This is a challenging course.  It has \"only\" 300 ft of elevation change over a lap but you\'ll be gassed! Expect lap times to be approximately 9:00. There will be one proper run up and one regulation set of barriers.  The course is mainly hard pack dirt and grass and has the potential for \"peanut butter\" mud with torrential rains.  The race is held through the orchards of The Apple Farm in Victor, NY.

title: Cross in the Park 2011
description: Race will be held November 6, 2011 at Delaware Park right in the heart of Buffalo, NY. Held under USA Cycling event permit. Race held rain or shine.
course: The start and finish of the course will be near the stone bridge in Delaware Park. This bridge is located right off of Rumsey Road between Windsor Avenue and Rumsey Lane. This is a USA Cycling sanctioned CX race on a 2800 meter fully taped, enclosed UCI-type course.
registration: Mountain bikes are permitted as per USAC rules. Bar ends must be removed prior to the race. All riders need an approved helmet; riders under 18 need a signed parental consent form. All riders must have a USAC racing license or purchase a one-day license (category 4 only). UCI licenses also acceptable.For more information please contact Peter Canfield, or email at pcanfield@campuswheelworks.com. Entry Fee: $25 pre-register. Mail standard entry to: Peter Canfield 744 Elmwood Ave. Buffalo, NY 14222. Day of race registration begins at 09:30 AM. PLEASE pre-registration at www.Bikereg.com.
notes: Race will be similar to last year, featuring new barriers and slightly different terrain!
directions: Directions: From Toronto/Hamilton follow Queen Elizabeth Way West towards Niagara/Ft. Erie. Take a slight left at ON-405E (Continues as I-190S). Take Exit 11 onto 198. Exit Elmwood Ave. Turn Left onto N. Park Dr. Turn Right onto Lincloln Pkwy. Destination on left. From Rochester, NY take the I-490W to the I90W. Take exit 51W onto 33W to Buffalo. Exit on 198. Exit off of the 198W towards Buffalo State College. Mergo onto Elmwood Avenue. Turn Left onto Park Avenue followed by a right onto Lincoln Pkwy.
